2 mM L-glutamine, penicillin (20 units/ml), streptomycin (20 mg/ml)
Differentiation_protocol:
Cells are cultured
in 0.05 mg/ml collagen-coated flask as a cell density of
104 cells/cm2
. 10 lM all-trans-RA in DMEM:F12 (2%
fetal bovine serum) media was added one day after
the seeding of the cells. At the end of 11 days,
the cells were washed 3 times and incubated in
DMEM:F12 media in the presence of RA and 50 ng/ml
of BDNF was added to the cultures and incubated for
three days. Cell cycle test was performed via the use
of flow cytometry analysis to confirm differentiation after retinoic acid application  (The CyFlow Cube
6, Germany)

Medium_supplements: 2 mM L-glutamine, 50 IU/mL/50 μg/mL penicillin/streptomycin, 20 μg/mL gentamicin sulphate  and 1 μg/mL Fungizone/amphotericin B
Differentiation_medium: MEM (DM I, Day 0); Neurobasal medium minus phenol red (DM II, Day 3))
Differentiation_supplements: 2 mM L-glutamine, 50 IU/mL/50 μg/mL penicillin/streptomycin (DM I);  2 mM Glutamax I, 1x B-27 supplement, 20 mM KCl, 50 IU/mL/50 μg/mL penicillin/streptomycin  and 50 ng/mL Human BDNF (DM II)
Differentiation_protocol:
The differentiation of the SH-SY5Y cells was carried out in two steps using phase 1
(DM I) and phase 2 (DM II) media. The DM I medium was MEM containing 2.5% (v/v) hiFBS, 2 mM L-glutamine, 50 IU/mL/50 μg/mL penicillin/streptomycin. The DM I was supplemented with
10 μM RA  immediately before adding the
medium to the cells (day 0). The DM II medium was Neurobasal
medium minus phenol red, supplemented with 2 mM Glutamax I, 1x B-27 supplement , 20 mM KCl ,
and 50 IU/mL/50 μg/mL penicillin/streptomycin . The DM II was supplemented with 10 μM RA and 50 ng/mL Human BDNF immediately before adding the
medium to the cells (Day 3).

Differentiation_protocol:
The differentiation of the SH-SY5Y cells was carried out in two steps using phase 1
(DM I) and phase 2 (DM II) media. The DM I medium was MEM containing 2.5% (v/v) hiFBS, 2 mM L-glutamine, 50 IU/mL/50 μg/mL penicillin/streptomycin. The DM I was supplemented with
10 μM RA  immediately before adding the
medium to the cells (day 0). The DM II medium was Neurobasal
medium minus phenol red, supplemented with 2 mM Glutamax I, 1x B-27 supplement , 20 mM KCl ,
and 50 IU/mL/50 μg/mL penicillin/streptomycin . The DM II was supplemented with 10 μM RA and 50 ng/mL Human BDNF immediately before adding the
medium to the cells (Day 3).
